results.name: Inverse function for injection A219650.
comment: a(0)=0; thereafter if n occurs as a term of A219650, a(n)=its position in A219650, otherwise zero. This works as an "inverse" function for A219650 in a sense that a(A219650(n)) = n for all n.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10079
xref: Cf. A219650, A230423, A230424. A219658 gives the positions of zeros after the first one. Analogous sequence for binary system: A213714.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Oct 31 2013
